le through GitHub and Maven. It includes/references the recently released H=
amcrest 1.3.

It would help us a great deal if some of you could give it a =
try and provide feedback. In particular, if you make heavy use of assertTha=
t and Hamcrest matchers, please report any incompatibilities that you might=
 experience.

Cheers, Marc
